# dotfiles — AI Agent Rules

## Project identity

Personal dotfiles managed by [chezmoi](https://www.chezmoi.io/). Bash-based CLI utilities use [options.bash](https://github.com/uhop/options.bash) for option parsing and rich terminal output. Targets Ubuntu (Debian) and macOS.

## Critical rules

- **Bash 4.0+** for all shell scripts. Start with `#!/usr/bin/env bash`.
- **`set -euCo pipefail`** and **`shopt -s expand_aliases`** at the top of every utility.
- **Do not add comments or remove comments** unless explicitly asked.
- All CLI utilities source options.bash via `. ~/.local/libs/main.sh`.
- **`args_cleaned` is an array.** Use `set -- "${args_cleaned[@]}"` (not `eval set -- "${args_cleaned}"`).
- Templates (`.tmpl`) use Go template syntax with chezmoi data (`osIdLike`, `hasGui`, etc.).
- Files in `.chezmoiignore` are not deployed to target machines.
- `doas` is aliased to `sudo` when available.

## Chezmoi naming

- `dot_` → `.` (e.g., `dot_bashrc` → `~/.bashrc`)
- `private_` → restricted permissions
- `executable_` → `chmod +x`
- `.tmpl` suffix → Go template with chezmoi data
- `run_onchange_before_` / `run_once_after_` → lifecycle scripts

## Code style

- 2-space indentation (`.editorconfig`).
- `echoRun` / `echoRun --bold` for colored command execution.
- `ansi::out` / `ansi::err` for terminal-aware output.
- ANSI globals (`RED`, `BOLD`, `RESET_ALL`, etc.) available via `main.sh`.
- Platform guards: `{{ if eq .osIdLike "linux-debian" }}` / `{{ if eq .osIdLike "darwin" }}`.

## CLI utility pattern

```bash
#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euCo pipefail
shopt -s expand_aliases
. ~/.local/libs/main.sh
script_dir="$(dirname "$(readlink -f "$0")")"
script_name=$(basename "$0")
args::program "$script_name" "1.0" "Description"
args::option "-v, --version" "Show version"
args::option "-h, --help" "Show help"
args::parse "$@"
set -- "${args_cleaned[@]}"
```

## File layout

- Shell config: `dot_bashrc`, `dot_bash_aliases`, `dot_bash_profile`, `dot_profile`
- App configs: `dot_config/` (alacritty, cheat, fastfetch, ghostty, git, kitty, micro, nano, tmux)
- CLI utilities: `private_dot_local/bin/executable_*` (arx, cln, goup, jot, upd, ollama-sync, etc.)
- Bootstrap: `private_dot_local/libs/main.sh` (auto-updates options.bash, sources core modules)
- JS helpers: `private_dot_local/bin/*.js` (nvm-utils, semver-utils, comp-utils)
- Vendors: `private_dot_local/vendors/fzf-git.sh`
- Package install: `run_onchange_before_install-packages.sh.tmpl`

## When reading the codebase

- Start with `ARCHITECTURE.md` for the project map.
- `AGENTS.md` has the full rules and conventions.
- `llms.txt` is a compact reference of all utilities and their options.
